name: Mahaanui Cottage Farmstay Experience, Gisborne NZ
description:
Mahaanui Cottage is a fully furnished, self-contained, private, country cottage located in the beautiful Tiniroto, halfway between Gisborne (~2.5 hr drive) and Wairoa (~1.5 hr drive). With everything you need for an enjoyable stay, it's perfect for friends and families looking for a relaxing country break. Or an active farm experience.

Drive from Auckland Airport - 8 hrs.
Drive from Napier Airport - 3 hrs.
Drive from Gisborne Airport - 2.5 hrs.

Note: Drive times are longer due to Cyclone G.
neighborhood_overview:
Doneraille Park is 2 minutes drive away. The park is a popular picnic, camping and swimming spot on our Hangaroa River.

The secret waterfall is 10 minutes drive down the road. It is a lovely picnic spot that locals enjoy. In the Summer, you can slide off the waterfall, jump in from the rocks and from behind the falls themselves.

There is private farm access for trout fishing, swimming or kayaking.

Some other nearby landmarks to check out include the Hackfalls Arboretum, Eastwood Hill Arboretum, Rere Rockslide and Te Reinga Falls / Ruakituri Valley – well known for its excellent trout fishing (Currently No Access - Te Reinga Bridge Destroyed in Cyclone Gabrielle).
host_about: Simon and I own Mahaanui, a 615 hectare hill country sheep and beef farm in Tiniroto, near Gisborne. We also host guests from NZ and around the world in our Mahaanui cottage and Mahaanui Quarters. We love including them in our farm activities and teaching visitors about farm practices, stock and land management as well as introducing them to our work dogs and pet animals.

name: CHEESEMAKERS RETREAT. Coastal Getaway.
description:
Cheesemakers Retreat is set within the garden of the hosts home. Guests have their own private area screened from the rest of the property. Studio is self contained. Te Awanga Beach is accessible via a landscaped pathway down the side of our own house (about 30metres). The shingle beach is nicer at low tide.

We are small dog friendly. (Charge applies)
neighborhood_overview:
Te Awanga started life as a beach house settlement for people from Napier and Hastings in the 1950s. During the last 40 years it has become a thriving community of people who permanently live here. The community as such has been retained by having one road in and one road out. The road through Te Awanga ends at Clifton, the main departure point for the trip to the Gannet Colony. If you are walking to the Cape, be sure and check the tides.

The Village is generally crime free but please lock doors and cars as an extra precaution. Warm summer nights often see locals enjoying an after dark walk. Dont worry they don't bight!

name: Hidden gem - best of two worlds.
description:
An historic cottage in a sheltered dell in the country near Makara Beach, fully restored Te whare iti is 10-15 minutes walk from the rugged Makara coast and roughly 35 minutes from the Wellington CBD. The preserved exterior enfolds very clean, warm and comfortable modern amenities.

Importantly- you must provide your own transport as there is no public transport to Makara from Karori the nearest suburb, some 9.5 kms away. Makara is true NZ countryside with a windy, narrow road to match!.
neighborhood_overview: A variety of coastal walks to suit any degree of endeavour or fitness including the famous Makara Walkway. This combines spectacular long-range views with a walk along a wild, west coast beach. Te whare iti is also very close to the West Wind wind-farm visitor centre boasting world-class views of the rugged Makara coast and South Island. Get close-up and personal with a 111 metre turbine!   Twitchers will not be disappointed with the local bird-life.  Rock fishing and surf casting are popular on this coast as is  diving and snorkelling.
